build checklist.
This provides bootstrap sequence in bottom-up order.

1. To setup base OS (assuming debian-based) to be able to conduct build:
   $ sudo apt-get install git make gcc texinfo g++ gawk bison

2. edit nix-from-scratch/configure.sh if necessary.

   $ cd nix-from-scratch
   $ ./configure.sh --prefix=$HOME/nixroot \
                    --nix-prefix=$HOME/nixroot \
                    --nxfs-toolchain-prefix=$HOME/nxfs-toolchain \
                    --nxfs-max-jobs=4

   Caveat on nxfs-max-jobs: can run into trouble if memory is limited;
   linker can use a lot more memory than individual compile steps.
   Setting this to Memory/8GB should be safe.  Memory/2GB is not sufficient.

   accept default, or replace values for
     PREFIX      (install prefix for software built along the way to compiling nixcpp itself)
     NIX_PREFIX  (keep the realpath transform, it's load-bearing for nix)

3. build dependencies, from source code, in bottom-up order.
